{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ghee into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add flour, semolina and sugar and mix <nobr>6 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 50 g of the coconut milk and knead <nobr>1 min\/<\/nobr>.","Add egg yolk, vanilla and remaining 20 g coconut milk and knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer onto a silicone bread mat or a lightly floured work surface and shape into a ball. Place a damp kitchen towel over dough and leave to rest for a minimum of 2 hours.","Using a rolling pin, thinly roll out dough (3 mm thickness), then cut into squares (5 x 5 cm). Working 1 square at a time, bring diagonal corners together and twist ends together. Bring remaining 2 diagonal corners together and twist ends together to seal.","Line a large plate with paper towel and set aside.","Place a large saucepan over high heat and add oil (8 cm deep). Heat oil to 170°C (see Tips). Working in batches, carefully lower kormolas into hot oil using a slotted spoon. Fry for 30-40 seconds, until golden brown. Transfer onto prepared plate and dust with icing sugar before serving. "]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g ghee (see Tips)","125 g plain flour","30 g semolina","30 g sugar","70 g coconut milk","1 egg yolk","½ tsp natural vanilla extract","oil, for frying","icing sugar, for decorating"]}],"id":"r132146","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-iY4QIJSrzW0\/XZWfBlLIxSI\/AAAAAAAAe9k\/5QxjcO1LypQcWdo4X-c4UQn2UR0cjoRMwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mVwRCwQSa5sxZAnT.png","title":"Kormolas (Kulkuls)","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.5 g","fat":"5.5 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"3.5 g","calories":"271 kJ \/ 66 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, kitchen towel, rolling pin, large plate, paper towel, large saucepan, slotted spoon, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own ghee, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","To chec